page.title: 16CHADWICK END
page.content: Chadwick End is a small village.There is a Post Office which is a food store at the same time.Next door is an antique shop.Near that is a restaurant called Ye Olde Bakehouse over the Warwick Road is a pub called the Orange Tree Inn.Opposite there is a Working Mens Club.There is a gararge next to the cross road.In Netherwood Lane is a church called Chadwick End Free Church.Near the gararge is a police house.Arden cottage is an interesting old building it was probably named after the forest of Arden.The only new houses are in Wheeler Close.
